.PP
You can use the \f[CR]result\f[R] event in an
\f[CR]addEventListener\f[R] method:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] recognition = \f[B]new\f[R] SpeechRecognition();

recognition.addEventListener(\[dq]result\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] color = event.results[0][0].transcript;
  diagnostic.textContent = \[ga]Result received: ${color}.\[ga];
  bg.style.backgroundColor = color;
});
.EE
.PP
Or use the \f[CR]onresult\f[R] event handler property:
.IP
.EX
recognition.onresult = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] color = event.results[0][0].transcript;
  diagnostic.textContent = \[ga]Result received: ${color}.\[ga];
  bg.style.backgroundColor = color;
};
.EE
